            </summary>
        <content type="html">
            <![CDATA[
                    <p><img src="https://wavycactus.github.io/media/posts/6/photo-1711409645921-ef3db0501f96.jpeg" class="type:primaryImage" alt="" /></p>
                <h3 class="subtitle subtitle-HEEcLo" dir="auto"><strong>Risorse aggiuntive</strong></h3>
<figure class="post__image"><img loading="lazy"  src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1711409645921-ef3db0501f96?crop=entropy&amp;cs=tinysrgb&amp;fit=max&amp;fm=jpg&amp;ixid=M3wzMDAzMzh8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHw1fHxicmFpbnxlbnwwfHx8fDE3NTc0NTE3NDZ8MA&amp;ixlib=rb-4.1.0&amp;q=80&amp;w=1080" alt="a close up of a human brain on a black background" width="702" height="395" data-is-external-image="true"></figure>
<p>Oltre alle letture consigliate nella lista di <a href="https://github.com/DifferentGlasses/PolyMathNow?tab=readme-ov-file" rel="nofollow ugc noopener">DifferentGlasses</a>, sembra interessante aggiungere:</p>
<h3 class="header-anchor-post">Fondamenta scientifiche (come funziona la mente quando apprendiamo)</h3>
<div class="pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent">
<div class="pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA">
<div id="§fondamenta-scientifiche-come-funziona-la-mente-quando-apprendiamo" class="pencraft pc-reset header-anchor offset-top"></div>
<button class="pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o" tabindex="0" type="button" aria-label="Link" data-href="https://wavycactus123.substack.com/i/173320089/fondamenta-scientifiche-come-funziona-la-mente-quando-apprendiamo"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewbox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-link"><path d="M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71"></path><path d="M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71"></path></svg></button></div>
</div>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Make It Stick</strong> — Brown, Roediger, McDaniel (2014). Il testo-chiave sulle tecniche evidence-based: recupero attivo, spaziatura, interleaving. Perfetto per impostare un metodo robusto. <code>(da leggere)</code></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Imparare. Il talento del cervello, la sfida delle macchine</strong> — Stanislas Dehaene (ed. it. Cortina, 2019). Neuroscienze dell’apprendimento spiegate con chiarezza: sonno, attenzione, feedback, errori. Ottimo ponte tra cervello e pratica.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>How Learning Works (2nd ed., 2023)</strong> — Ambrose et al. Cornice in 8 principi su come le persone apprendono; utilissimo anche per auto-formazione sul lavoro.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Understanding How We Learn</strong> — Y. Weinstein, M. Sumeracki, O. Caviglioli (2018). Sintesi operativa delle strategie migliori (retrieval, spacing, dual coding). <code>(da leggere)</code></p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="header-anchor-post">Tecniche di studio pratiche (cosa fare, passo per passo)</h3>
<div class="pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent">
<div class="pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA">
<div id="§tecniche-di-studio-pratiche-cosa-fare-passo-per-passo" class="pencraft pc-reset header-anchor offset-top"></div>
<button class="pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o" tabindex="0" type="button" aria-label="Link" data-href="https://wavycactus123.substack.com/i/173320089/tecniche-di-studio-pratiche-cosa-fare-passo-per-passo"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewbox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-link"><path d="M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71"></path><path d="M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71"></path></svg></button></div>
</div>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Outsmart Your Brain (2023)</strong> — Daniel T. Willingham. Smonta abitudini illusorie (evidenziare, rileggere) e propone routine efficaci per prendere appunti, memorizzare, preparare esami e presentazioni.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Learn Better (2017)</strong> — Ulrich Boser. Sei passi per studiare meglio con esempi concreti; ottimo per chi rientra in formazione adulta.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>A Mind for Numbers (2014)</strong> — Barbara Oakley (in italiano: <em>Una mente per i numeri</em>, Logus, 2020). Metodo pratico per argomenti “duri”, ma applicabile a qualunque materia.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="header-anchor-post">Pratica deliberata &amp; sviluppo di competenze (diventare davvero bravi)</h3>
<div class="pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent">
<div class="pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA">
<div id="§pratica-deliberata-and-sviluppo-di-competenze-diventare-davvero-bravi" class="pencraft pc-reset header-anchor offset-top"></div>
<button class="pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o" tabindex="0" type="button" aria-label="Link" data-href="https://wavycactus123.substack.com/i/173320089/pratica-deliberata-and-sviluppo-di-competenze-diventare-davvero-bravi"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewbox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-link"><path d="M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71"></path><path d="M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71"></path></svg></button></div>
</div>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Peak (2016)</strong> — K. Anders Ericsson &amp; Robert Pool. La ricerca “madre” su deliberate practice, rappresentazioni mentali e feedback mirato. Ideale per abilità professionali e tecniche.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Talent Is Overrated (2008)</strong> — Geoff Colvin. Perché il “talento” non basta e come progettare pratica intenzionale nel lavoro.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>The Art of Learning (2007)</strong> — Josh Waitzkin. Approccio mentale alla performance (dallo sport agli scacchi al lavoro). Ispirazionale ma concreto.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="header-anchor-post">Focus, abitudini e sistema personale (come creare le condizioni per imparare)</h3>
<div class="pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent">
<div class="pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA">
<div id="§focus-abitudini-e-sistema-personale-come-creare-le-condizioni-per-imparare" class="pencraft pc-reset header-anchor offset-top"></div>
<button class="pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o" tabindex="0" type="button" aria-label="Link" data-href="https://wavycactus123.substack.com/i/173320089/focus-abitudini-e-sistema-personale-come-creare-le-condizioni-per-imparare"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewbox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-link"><path d="M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71"></path><path d="M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71"></path></svg></button></div>
</div>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Deep Work (2016)</strong> — Cal Newport. Regole per proteggere il focus profondo: essenziale se studi/lavori in ambienti pieni di distrazioni.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Atomic Habits (2018)</strong> — James Clear. Costruire (e mantenere) abitudini che supportano lo studio quotidiano; super pratico.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="header-anchor-post">Metapprendimento, progetti intensivi &amp; range</h3>
<div class="pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent">
<div class="pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA">
<div id="§metapprendimento-progetti-intensivi-and-range" class="pencraft pc-reset header-anchor offset-top"></div>
<button class="pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o" tabindex="0" type="button" aria-label="Link" data-href="https://wavycactus123.substack.com/i/173320089/metapprendimento-progetti-intensivi-and-range"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewbox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-link"><path d="M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71"></path><path d="M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71"></path></svg></button></div>
</div>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Ultralearning (2019)</strong> — Scott H. Young. Nove principi per progetti di auto-apprendimento accelerato (lingue, software, skill tecniche). <code>(da leggere)</code></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Range (2019)</strong> — David Epstein. Perché esperienze diverse aiutano a risolvere problemi “mal definiti” e imparare meglio sul lavoro.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="header-anchor-post">Memoria &amp; creatività</h3>
<div class="pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-parent">
<div class="pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA">
<div id="§memoria-and-creativita" class="pencraft pc-reset header-anchor offset-top"></div>
<button class="pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton-mq_Et5 iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonStyle-r7yGCK size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o" tabindex="0" type="button" aria-label="Link" data-href="https://wavycactus123.substack.com/i/173320089/memoria-and-creativita"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewbox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-link"><path d="M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71"></path><path d="M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71"></path></svg></button></div>
